    "source_latex": "% BEGIN TZP DERIVATION LAYER\n\\tzpsection{Derivation Layer}\n\\paragraph{Primary Equations.}\n\\begin{equation}\nP \\longrightarrow M,\n\\qquad\n\\mathrm{Struct}(P)=SO(3)\\times U(1).\n\\end{equation}\n\n\\begin{equation}\n\\sigma:M\\longrightarrow P.\n\\end{equation}\n\n\\paragraph{Primary Derivation.}\nLet $M$ be the base manifold of admissible configurations. Rotational orientation is represented by $SO(3)$, while gauge phase is represented by $U(1)$.\n\nA bundle carrying both data has structure group:\n\\begin{equation}\nSO(3)\\times U(1).\n\\end{equation}\n\nThus,\n\\begin{equation}\nP\\to M,\n\\qquad\n\\mathrm{Struct}(P)=SO(3)\\times U(1).\n\\end{equation}\n\nA physical configuration is then a section:\n\\begin{equation}\n\\boxed{\n\\sigma:M\\to P.\n}\n\\end{equation}\n\n\\paragraph{Interpretation.}\nRotational and gauge-phase data are organized into one configuration bundle.\n% END TZP DERIVATION LAYER"
